  "prompt": "What is the best way to get change for the new 2000 INR note?",
  "response": "Getting change for the new \u20b92000 INR note can sometimes be a challenge due to its high denomination. Here are some effective ways to break it into smaller denominations:\n\n### 1. **Visit a Bank**\n   - Approach your nearest bank branch and request to exchange the \u20b92000 note for smaller denominations. This is the most reliable and formal method.\n   - Carry a valid ID proof (Aadhaar card, PAN card, etc.) as banks may require it for high-denomination exchanges.\n\n### 2. **Use an ATM**\n   - Withdraw smaller denominations from an ATM. Many ATMs dispense \u20b9500, \u20b9200, and \u20b9100 notes.\n   - Look for ATMs that explicitly mention dispensing smaller denominations.\n\n### 3. **Ask at Retail Stores or Supermarkets**\n   - Large retail stores, supermarkets, or shopping malls often have sufficient cash reserves and may be willing to provide change for a \u20b92000 note.\n   - Make a small purchase and request the balance in smaller notes.\n\n### 4. **Petrol Pumps**\n   - Petrol pumps frequently deal with cash transactions and may be able to provide change for a \u20b92000 note, especially if you fill fuel for that amount.\n\n### 5. **Public Transport or Taxi Services**\n   - If you use public transport or hire a taxi, you can request change when paying with a \u20b92000 note. However, ensure they have sufficient change before handing over the note.\n\n### 6. **Local Markets or Street Vendors**\n   - Small vendors or marketplaces may be hesitant due to the high value of the note, but some may agree to provide change if you make a purchase.\n\n### 7. **Currency Exchange Counters**\n   - Some currency exchange counters or authorized money changers may help break the \u20b92000 note into smaller denominations.\n\n### 8. **Digital Payment Apps**\n   - If you\u2019re unable to get change, consider using digital payment methods (UPI, Paytm, etc.) for transactions and keep the \u20b92000 note for emergencies or larger purchases.\n\n### Tips:\n   - Always ensure the authenticity of the notes you receive in exchange.\n   - Avoid approaching strangers or informal sources to prevent scams.\n   - Be polite and patient when requesting change, as not everyone may have sufficient reserves.\n\nBy using these methods, you should be able to break your \u20b92000 note into smaller denominations with ease.",
